The Senator representing Osun Central, Dr. Ajibola Basiru and five judges of the state’s judiciary have gone into self-isolation in response to their recent return from overseas. The state Commissioner for Health, Dr. Rafiu Isamotu, confirmed this in a chat with Daily Trust. “The Senator and the judges are in self-isolation and we are monitoring them. They have not been tested because they are not showing any symptom of COVID-19,” he said. COVID-19: Osun Senator, 5  judges in self-isolation Before testing positive for COVID-19, Kyari mingled with govs, ministers, others Senator Adeleke arraigned, granted bail on self-recognition